HEADWORD: Canaille
<hw>Ca*naille"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>canaille</ets> (cf. It. <ets>canaglia</ets>), prop. and orig. a
pack of dogs, fr. L. <ets>Canis</ets> dog.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
lowest class of people; the rabble; the vulgar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Shorts or inferior flour.</def>
<mark>[Canadian]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

